description:
The following is a method of SyncSetInputFromSubscriber

	private void handleChange(IResource resource) {		
		try {
			collect(resource, (IProgressMonitor)null);
		} catch (TeamException e) {
			log(e);
		}
	}

It logs any exceptions that occur. This could be dangerous as what is 
displayed to the user will be wrong but the feedback that there was a problem 
is subtle.

build eclipse 3.0 M3 (20030826)

Eclipse scenario:
1) Open CVS perspective
2) Ensure that you one repository configured and its has not tag configured (the
branches list has to empty)
3) Expanded the Branch list in the CVS Repository view

Tree view model is corrupted.

-> The bug is caused by disposing the last TreeItem of another TreeItem during
its expanded callback.

Test case:
public static void main(String[] args) {
	DeviceData data = new DeviceData();
	data.debug = true;
	final Display display = new Display(data);
	final Shell shell = new Shell(display);
	Tree tree = new Tree(shell, SWT.BORDER);
	final TreeItem item1 = new TreeItem(tree, SWT.NONE);
	item1.setText("Test1");
	final TreeItem subItem = new TreeItem(item1, SWT.NONE);
	subItem.setText("sub Test");
	tree.addListener(SWT.Expand, new Listener() {
		public void handleEvent(Event event) {
			subItem.dispose();
			System.out.println("sub item disposed");
		}
	});
	tree.setBounds(10, 10, 180, 180);
	shell.setBounds(200, 200, 300, 300);
	shell.open();
	while (!shell.isDisposed()) {
		if (!display.readAndDispatch())
			display.sleep();
	}
	display.dispose();
}


-> Last note, this bug was introduced when the signal expanded_row was replaced
by the signal test_row_expanded
